                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d832">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">390D.1115/121: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-15T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 15, 1941—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>299. Now that the armistice has been signed the Department may wish to inform
                    inquirers that as far as I have been able to ascertain all American citizens in
                    Syria and the Lebanon are well and the properties of American institutions have
                    suffered no damage.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
